    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-06-26T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-06-26T01:00:00-05:00" n="237"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d237">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7115: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Second Secretary of Legation in China</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Atcheson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-06-26T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >June 26, 1935—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 26—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>183. Suma of Japanese Embassy indicated to Counselor Lockhart and me in
                    conversation this morning that he considered Sino-Japanese issues in Hopei
                    completely settled and said that there was now no question of an exchange of
                    memoranda between Japanese and Chinese or the signing of any kind of document by
                    them and Chinese in that connection. He stated that the Chahar question would be
                    taken up in Nanking within a few days, the details having been worked out in the
                    North and the Chinese Government having already agreed in principle to the
                    points suggested by the Japanese.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Atcheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
